-- Berkshire reports lower stakes in 2 railroads
-- 
-- Mon Oct 15, 2007 7:01pm EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2007/10/15/us-berkshire-railroads-idUSN1538054720071015

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Warren Buffett's Berkshire Hathaway Inc ( BRKa.N )( BRKb.N ), which has accumulated a 17.2 percent stake in Burlington Northern Santa Fe Corp BNI.N, reported on Monday it reduced stakes in two other railroads -- Norfolk Southern Corp ( NSC.N ) and Union Pacific Corp ( UNP.N ). 

 In a regulatory filing, Berkshire reported a stake of 3.76 million shares in Norfolk Southern as of June 30, down from 6.36 million shares on March 31. It also reported a stake of 7.41 million shares in Union Pacific as of June 30, down from 10.51 million shares March 31. (Reporting by Jonathan Stempel, editing by Jeffrey Benkoe)